      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear u, but i've seen so many people in my hiking groups doing high dose protocols like this to stay healthy in the dark months. it seems like a pretty standard thing to do when you're deficient. isn't it true that these high doses are actually used in clinical settings for people with severe deficiencies, so doing it for just a few weeks shouldn't be that different? feels like i'm just being overly cautious if i'm already sure my levels are low.",
